===Noun===
{{en-noun|-}}

# {{lb|en|inorganic compound}} The ammonium [[salt]] of [[nitric acid]], NH<sub>4</sub>NO<sub>3</sub>; it is used in [[fertilizer]]s and [[explosive]]s (notoriously in [[improvised explosive device]]s, though its main importance is as an explosive in its own right and in mixtures such as [[amatol]] and [[ANFO]]).
#* {{quote-journal|en|author=John Ismay|title=What Is Ammonium Nitrate, Blamed in the Beirut Explosion?|work=The New York Times|date=2020-08-05|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/08/05/world/middleeast/beirut-explosion-ammonium-nitrate.html|issn=0362-4331|passage=According to the Lebanese government, about 2,750 tons of '''ammonium nitrate''' fertilizer was stored in a warehouse on the Beirut waterfront and caught fire, later exploding.}}

